Annotation

Mandatory step for DESeq2 object preparation.

Row <- data.frame(Raw[, 21])
GeneID <- substr(Row[, 1], 1, 17)
Row$Symbol <- mapIds(org.Mm.eg.db,
                     keys = GeneID,
                     column = 'SYMBOL',
                     keytype = 'SYMBOL')
Row$Entrez <- mapIds(org.Mm.eg.db,
                     keys = GeneID,
                     column = 'ENTREZID',
                     keytype = 'SYMBOL',
                     multiVals = 'first')
## 'select()' returned 1:1 mapping between keys and columns

Arranging DESeq2 object

We have two variables of interest here: side (contra vs ipsi) and genotype (KO vs WT). We’ll want four main comparisons: IpsiKO vs IpsiWT, ContraKO vs ContraWT, ContraWT vs IpsiWT and ContraKO vs IpsiKO. The design matrix will be done to reflect this.

Set <- data.frame(Raw, row.names = 21)
Set_Mat <- as.matrix(Set[, 9:20])
ColData <- data.frame(Samples = 1:12,
                      ID = c('WI_1', 'WI_2', 'WI_3', 'WC_1', 'WC_2', 'WC_3',
                             'DI_1', 'DI_2', 'DI_3', 'DC_1', 'DC_2', 'DC_3'),
                      Genotype = factor(c(rep('WT', 6),
                                          rep('KO', 6)),
                                        levels = c('WT', 'KO')),
                      Side = factor(c(rep('Ipsilateral', 3),
                                      rep('Contralateral', 3),
                                      rep('Ipsilateral', 3),
                                      rep('Contralateral', 3)),
                                    levels = c('Contralateral', 'Ipsilateral')),
                      Replicate = c(1, 2, 3, 1, 2, 3, 1, 2, 3, 1, 2, 3)) %>%
  column_to_rownames(var = 'ID')
all(rownames(ColData) == colnames(Set_Mat))
## [1] TRUE
ColData$Group <- factor(paste0(ColData$Side, ColData$Genotype),
                        levels = c('ContralateralWT', 'IpsilateralWT',
                                   'ContralateralKO', 'IpsilateralKO'))
ColData

Applying DESeq2 model

We apply a Wald test to ID differentially expressed genes. We use a logFoldChange of 0 looking for a simple difference.

DE_Set <- DESeq(DE_Set, test = 'Wald')

Getting results

We perform contrasts here.

# IpsiWT vs ContraWT
res_WI_WC <- results(DE_Set, contrast = cont_WI_WC, alpha = FDR,
                     lfcThreshold = LFC)
res_WI_WC <- res_WI_WC %>%
  data.frame() %>%
  rownames_to_column(var = 'Gene') %>%
  as_tibble()
colnames(res_WI_WC)[c(3, 7)] <- c('WI_WC_log2FC',
                                  'WI_WC_padj')

# ContraKO vs ContraWT
res_DC_WC <- results(DE_Set, contrast = cont_DC_WC, alpha = FDR,
                     lfcThreshold = LFC)
res_DC_WC <- res_DC_WC %>%
  data.frame() %>%
  rownames_to_column(var = 'Gene') %>%
  as_tibble()
colnames(res_DC_WC)[c(3, 7)] <- c('DC_WC_log2FC',
                                  'DC_WC_padj')

# IpsiKO vs ContraWT
res_DI_WC <- results(DE_Set, contrast = cont_DI_WC, alpha = FDR,
                     lfcThreshold = LFC)
res_DI_WC <- res_DI_WC %>%
  data.frame() %>%
  rownames_to_column(var = 'Gene') %>%
  as_tibble()
colnames(res_DI_WC)[c(3, 7)] <- c('DI_WC_log2FC',
                                  'DI_WC_padj')

# Ipsi KO vs Ipsi WT
DE_Set$Group <- relevel(DE_Set$Group, ref = 'IpsilateralWT')
DE_Set <- nbinomWaldTest(DE_Set)
## found results columns, replacing these
res_DI_WI <- results(DE_Set, contrast = cont_DI_WI, alpha = FDR,
                     lfcThreshold = LFC)

# Ipsi KO vs ContraKO

DE_Set <- nbinomWaldTest(DE_Set)

Curating dataset for visualisation

Putting results back to TPM table and filtering to keep only protein-coding genes and ID DEGs.Note that the statistical tests were done on normalized raw count data, not TPM. We however prefer to use TPM for visualizations as it’s a more stable, recognized unit.

Diff_set <- Tpm %>%
  inner_join(res_WI_WC[, c(1, 3, 7)]) %>%
  inner_join(res_DC_WC[, c(1, 3, 7)]) %>%
  inner_join(res_DI_WC[, c(1, 3, 7)]) %>%
  inner_join(res_DI_WI[, c(1, 3, 7)]) %>%
  inner_join(res_DI_DC[, c(1, 3, 7)]) %>%
  filter(str_detect(Annotation, 'protein-coding'))
## Joining with `by = join_by(Gene)`
## Joining with `by = join_by(Gene)`
## Joining with `by = join_by(Gene)`
## Joining with `by = join_by(Gene)`
## Joining with `by = join_by(Gene)`
Diff_set <- Diff_set %>%
  mutate(WI_WC_Status = case_when(WI_WC_log2FC > LFC &
                                    WI_WC_padj < FDR ~ 'WI',
                                  WI_WC_log2FC < -LFC &
                                    WI_WC_padj < FDR ~ 'WC',
                                  TRUE ~ 'Not'),
         DC_WC_Status = case_when(DC_WC_log2FC > LFC &
                                    DC_WC_padj < FDR ~ 'DC',
                                  DC_WC_log2FC < -LFC &
                                    DC_WC_padj < FDR ~ 'WC',
                                  TRUE ~ 'Not'),
         DI_WC_Status = case_when(DI_WC_log2FC > LFC &
                                    DI_WC_padj < FDR ~ 'DI',
                                  DI_WC_log2FC < -LFC &
                                    DI_WC_padj < FDR ~ 'WC',
                                  TRUE ~ 'Not'),
         DI_WI_Status = case_when(DI_WI_log2FC > LFC &
                                    DI_WI_padj < FDR ~ 'DI',
                                  DI_WI_log2FC < -LFC &
                                    DI_WI_padj < FDR ~ 'WI',
                                  TRUE ~ 'Not'),
         DI_DC_Status = case_when(DI_DC_log2FC > LFC &
                                    DI_DC_padj < FDR ~ 'DI',
                                  DI_DC_log2FC < -LFC &
                                    DI_DC_padj < FDR ~ 'DC',
                                  TRUE ~ 'Not'))

Volcano plots

Five volcano plots are to be made. A series of 10 genes are set to be labelled for each plot, but keep in mind that DESeq2 sometimes does not compute an adjusted p-value for a comparison when the mean read count is very low (e.g., Dkk1 & Cd19 in the DI vs WI comparison). The label will not show up in those cases.

Labeled and unlabeled versions of the plots are provided. The labeled version will accurately pinpoint the genes, but positions of the labels are generated automatically and are difficult to control. The unlabeled version can serve to manually add lines and labels in Illustrator/Inkscape as in the provided plot, but with more convenient positions.

# Labelled genes
Labelled <- c('Dkk1', 'Cd19', 'Ly6d', 'Blk', 'Aspg',
              'Onecut1', 'Rnps1', 'Pou4f1', 'Fcrls', 'Iqgap3', 'Ccr6')
Diff_set <- Diff_set %>%
  mutate(Labels = ifelse(Gene %in% Labelled,
                         Gene,
                         ''))

# WI vs WC
Diff_set %>%
  ggplot(aes(WI_WC_log2FC, -log10(WI_WC_padj), fill = WI_WC_Status,
             label = Labels)) +
  geom_point(shape = 21, color = 'black', alpha = 0.8) +
  geom_hline(yintercept = -log10(FDR), linetype = 2) +
  xlab('log2(WI/WC)') +
  ylab('-log10(adjusted p-value)') +
  scale_y_continuous(limits = c(0, 30)) +
  scale_x_continuous(limits = c(-8, 8)) +
  scale_fill_manual(values = c('#a9a9a9',
                                        rgb(4, 51, 255, maxColorValue = 255),
                                        rgb(251, 1, 6, maxColorValue = 255))) +
  geom_label_repel(box.padding = 0.5,
                   force = 10,
                   max.overlaps = Inf,
                   fontface = 'italic') +
  theme_bw() +
  theme(legend.position = 'none',
        panel.grid = element_blank())

Heatmap

We need to get a matrix of TPM values for the selected genes for all samples, after which we will map the relative expression for each sample. Note that H2-Q5 is not detected in the dataset even though it was in the provided list. Further note that just because a gene is highly expressed in one condition versus the other in this graph does not mean the difference is statistically significant; refer to the table for this information.

Heat_genes <- c('H2-Q1', 'H2-Q10', 'H2-Q2', 'H2-Q4', 'H2-Q8', 'H2-T-ps',
                'H2-T10', 'H2-T24', 'H2-DMb2', 'Pdzk1ip1', 'Spib', 'Pax5',
                'Ms4a1', 'Fcmr', 'Cd19', 'Cd79a', 'Cd79b', 'Glp2r',
                'Slc5a5', 'Mef2b', 'Fpr2', 'Fam89a', 'Shox2', 'Glp1r', 'Nrk',
                'Tbx15', 'Asgr1')

Heat_set <- Diff_set %>%
  filter(Gene %in% Heat_genes) %>%
  mutate(Gene = factor(Gene, levels = Heat_genes)) %>%
  arrange(Gene)

Heat_mat <- as.matrix(Heat_set[, c(12:14, 9:11, 18:20, 15:17)])
rownames(Heat_mat) <- Heat_set$Gene
Annotations <- data.frame(Condition = factor(c(rep('WC', 3), 
                                               rep('WI', 3),
                                               rep('DC', 3),
                                               rep('DI', 3))))
rownames(Annotations) <- colnames(Heat_mat)
newnames <- lapply(rownames(Heat_mat),
                   function(x) bquote(italic(.(x))))
pheatmap(Heat_mat,
         scale = 'row',
         cluster_rows = FALSE,
         cluster_cols = FALSE,
         annotation_col = Annotations,
         annotation_names_col = FALSE,
         show_colnames = FALSE,
         labels_row = as.expression(newnames),
         filename = '230619_ElAli_Heat_relative.pdf',
         width = 4,
         height = 6)

Venn diagrams

Using WC as a control condition, two Venn diagrams are to be made: upregulated genes in each condition versus WC, and the same for downregulated genes.

Up_WI <- Diff_set %>%
  filter(WI_WC_Status == 'WI') %>%
  pull(Gene)
Up_DC <- Diff_set %>%
  filter(DC_WC_Status == 'DC') %>%
  pull(Gene)
Up_DI <- Diff_set %>%
  filter(DI_WC_Status == 'DI') %>%
  pull(Gene)
pdf('230307_ElAli_Venn_Up.pdf', 5, 4.5)
draw.triple.venn(length(Up_WI),
                 length(Up_DC),
                 length(Up_DI),
                 length(which(Up_WI %in% Up_DC)),
                 length(which(Up_DC %in% Up_DI)),
                 length(which(Up_WI %in% Up_DI)),
                 length(which(Up_WI %in% Up_DC & Up_WI %in% Up_DI)),
                 col = c(rgb(251, 1, 6, maxColorValue = 255),
                         rgb(4, 51, 255, maxColorValue = 255),
                         'brown'),
                 fill = c(alpha(rgb(251, 1, 6, maxColorValue = 255), 0.5),
                          alpha(rgb(4, 51, 255, maxColorValue = 255), 0.5),
                          alpha('brown', 0.5)),
                 category = c('Up WI', 'Up DC', 'Up DI'),
                 cex = 1.3,
                 cat.cex = 1.3,
                 fontfamily = 'sans',
                 cat.fontfamily = 'sans',
                 rotation.degree = 180,
                 cat.default.pos = 'outer')
